I cannot believe this happened. Two retreats just one week apart has me overwhelmed with love and awe. One day I will share how intense the journey was to launch these retreats. For those who know, miracles and faith are real!

Witnessing black women rest and laugh and connect like family and rest some more and reflect and eat good food and dance and rest some more and move on their mats and explore and rest some more and tap into mindfulness and breathe and just be and step more into their magic and allow Grenada to bless them ...I could go on but actually, there are no words. 

This is a part of my life's work. I feel inspired. I feel powerful. I feel grateful. I feel honored. I feel eager to host more of these profound experiences for more black women. This is the medicine. 

Fight for what you believe in and believe in what you are fighting for.  Everything else will follow.

Eff it. After hearing about what the Dalai Lama did...I'm gonna just focus on drinking my water, practicing my dance moves and minding my business cuz it's all just smoke and mirrors out there. Question everything. Find your own truth. 

This video is not a proposition; it's a celebration of my liberation. 

But also, I never evah evah evah would shake my tail feather because I was often one of the only black girls growing up and stereotypically didn't want to be labeled as the stereotype, you get me? So I would just two step. Unbeknownst to me, movements like this release trauma, ground energy, support creativity, fuel embodiment and ignite so many other magical, medicinal blessings. 

Shake your ass today. It will help with navigating the fuckery. Also, the news is trash. No solutions. Just trash. It's all a part of the plan to keep us stressed, depressed and fearful. 

The world is amazing. Go dance. Kiss a baby. Take a nap. Frolic in nature. Hug a tree. Meditate. Just go ✨

Also also...I was told that I actually need to let my booty shake more. Whew knew?!?! 

#justdance #dancelikenooneiswatching #moveyourbody #dance #soca #caribbeanmusic #movementismedicine #heal #findjoy #shakeitoff

In the words of Lauren Hill, "It could all be so simple, but you'd rather make it hard." That's how I feel about the deliberate disconnect the powers to be have created between we humans and our access to nature. "They" want us enslaved to a system that makes us work for food and shelter. How evil is that?! Meanwhile nature is over here wanting to give us everything we need and more. Sunday was so soft that I was able to reflect. 

I'm realizing that a big part of my work is helping others to remember. Whatever it is that they need to remember. Because I too had to remember. I'm always practicing to remember. To remember who I am. Before the programming. To remember how magical it all actually is. This maddening thing called life. 

Throwback to my first group of retreat ladies on our last evening together. We honored the elements and used a calabash to burn what we were ready to forget/release and what we were ready to remember/call in. It was wild witnessing how the papers burned differently when we put to flame what we were calling in. And then we dumped the ashes in the ocean. The end.

I didn't know what I needed until I found it. To think that it used to be illegal for a group of black folk to gather (Negro Act of 1740). And even now, in yt work spaces in particular, the awareness of this can still affect how we gather...if it's safe to gather...if a yt coworker will make it their mission to say something as we gather. It's still a thing. 

And now here we are, as the dreams our ancestors manifested, gathering together to celebrate the simple things like swinging underneath a tree as our sisters cheer us on. 

What a blessing to be here. Together we rise. More offerings for us to gather are on the way ✨

I celebrated another year around the sun yesterday, June 17th on a new moon to be exact! I was actually born on Father's Day many moons ago. Yesterday was a rainy, moody morning just the way I like it.  An annual ocean swim with my dog by my side (surveilling me from his land perch) has now become tradition. Very special humans graced me with their presence throughout the day. I kept it simple and small, the celebrations. Having a bday gathering is a practice for me. It's a practice of receiving love and adornment 🥹 I I ended the night dancing and sweating it all out. And then my shoe broke just as I was leaving the venue, my arm around my friend who helped me hobble to my car with glee. I think it's a good omen for a new year full of dancing hard and divine timing.  #Sheready

A special thank you to @asweetmellowdee @mccalmanco @memsor @idelu and many more for your blessings 💗🥳💃🏾

How I spent July 4th because...mango season 🥭✨

It's wild how little fruit trees there are in the States. Access is limited. I remember growing up with a grape vine and that was magical as a child. We also had two very sour tasting apple trees at my second childhood home which was hella random and rare. It was my chore to clean up the fallen mushy mess without getting stung by wasps and bees. To my teenage relief, the trees eventually were cut down. So now as an adult it feels so healing and fulfilling to reconnect with fruit trees in this way. To see the flowers that birth the fruit. To eat the fruit that was once a flower. 

This is freedom. 

#letfreedomring #freedom #mangoseason #juliemango #mangoes #mangolover #joy #abundance #mamanature #gratitude #thankyou #july4th

You know how Instagram is the highlight reel and what goes on behind the curated posts is rarely discussed? Well this Friday, July 7th @ 2pm EST @elsalovesyou and I will be chatting about the hot topic which is the neurodivergent journey and how to navigate keeping up in a neurotypical, goal oriented world. Perhaps our super power is the exact thing society tells us is a flaw. The struggle is real but there are tools to support our daily routine (that I am learning) so that we can continue manifesting our magic to share with the world.

One thing about me...I love me some cute clothes and the dopamine hit that my mind gets from shopping. It's top tier! Clothing actually brings me happiness.  Idk what they say, but you can buy happiness. I said what I said🤭

So yeah, when my hard tasks have been completed and it's time for a reward, you can find me scrolling for clothing. 

Most of these images are from 2018/2019 in an album on my phone titled, "I Miss Shopping" 😆😔🛍️
